channel.title: Error
channel.description:
well, ive recently updated my servers NPCdrop.cfg and AutoSpawn.cfg (i use richscape2/devolution 7) and whenever i open up runserver.bat i get this...
[code]Loading npcs... drops... Exception in thread "main" java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException: 45 at NPCHandler.loadNPCDrops(NPCHandler.java:1473) at NPCHandler.<init>(NPCHandler.java:426) at server.main(server.java:108)[/code]
does anyone know what this means?

When you were changing things in the autospawn, its possible you didn’t tab correctly. So copy the stuff you put in the autospawn, and delete compile and try again. IF that works, than pay attention on how the other autospawns are.
